#MemorialDay weekend.  Remembrances of #MilitaryPagan War Dead.

Sgt. Patrick Stewart (1970-2005) of Nevada was first #Wiccan killed in action in Operation Enduring Freedom in Afghanistan. 

Sgt. Stewart was a Desert Storm veteran. He was among those who returned to US Military service in 2001 after 9/11 attacks on USA. He & his crew mates were killed when enemy fire shot down the Chinook helicopter they were in providing cover for US troops on the ground.

His VA issued #Pentacle gravestone marks his grave at Veterans Ridge of #CircleSanctuary  national #Pagan cemetery in Wisconsin USA.

His widow & others were part of our #CircleSanctuary team supporting Veteran #PentacleQuest which resulted in #PaganRights victory in 2007. More about this @circlesanctuary website

Sgt. Stewart Memorial Marker at #CircleCemetery is one of the first Pentacle markers issued by US Department of Veterans Affairs.

#OrderofthePentacle was founded on #VeteransDay2006 as part of our efforts to have the #Pentacle authorized by US federal government for inclusion on gravestones the US Department of #VeteransAffairs issues to mark graves of deceased #Veterans in public & private cemeteries.

The #VeteranPentacleQuest met with success on April 23, 2007. 

In addition to the Pentacle, the #Heathen #ThorsHammer & #Druid #Awen symbols also have been added to the list of emblems of belief that are options to be included on VA issued gravestones marking graves of deceased veterans.

At our national #PaganCemetery at #CircleSanctuaryNaturePreserve, we have VA Pentacle & Awen inscribed markers on #VeteransRidge

#WaesHael! Ceremonial beverage, #Wassail, with #applecider & spices for #NewYear #TwelfthNight #Yuletide #Christmas #Solstice #Yule #Hogmanay & other #HappyHolidays Celebrations.

#Wassail or #WaesHael is #Saxon for #GoodHealth & is a ceremonial greeting.

#Wassail as a verb refers to #Wassailing aka going with a #WassailBowl in blessing #rituals in towns & orchards.

Ingredients in my #Wintertime Wassail: apple cider & powdered spices: cinnamon, all spice, cloves, nutmeg. I use good quality powdered spices & continue to stir them in as cider is heated.
